## 📊 User Roles & Dashboard Routing

After successful authentication, route user to correct dashboard based on `users.role`:

| Role | Value in DB | Route To | Access Level |
|------|-------------|----------|--------------|
| **Parent** | `parent` | Parent Dashboard | Book sessions, approve enrollments, manage children |
| **Private Educator** | `special_educator` | Educator Dashboard | Manage profile, offerings, conduct sessions |
| **School Admin** | `school_admin` | School Admin Panel | Manage school, teachers, billing, custom games |
| **School Teacher** | `school_teacher` | Teacher Dashboard | Manage classrooms, students, track progress |
| **Platform Admin** | `admin` | Admin Dashboard | Full platform access, all management |
| **Manufacturer** | `manufacturer` | Manufacturer Portal | View device analytics, royalties |

### **Role Detection in FlutterFlow:**

```dart
// After successful login, query user role
final user = Supabase.instance.client.auth.currentUser;
final userData = await Supabase.instance.client
  .from('users')
  .select('role')
  .eq('id', user.id)
  .single();

String role = userData['role'];

// Route based on role
if (role == 'parent') {
  Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/parent-dashboard');
} else if (role == 'special_educator') {
  Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/educator-dashboard');
} else if (role == 'school_admin') {
  Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/school-admin');
} // ... etc
```

